const cfcLetterExplanation = `<dl class="modal-dl">
  <dd>
    <h3>Countering Financial Crime Letter</h3>

    <p>Where a Countering Financial Crime Letter has been requested, this is because Zeta Fund Services Limited ("Zeta") is required to assess your internal controls as part of the onboarding process.</p>

    <p>An example of this is a regulated nominee company looking to invest of behalf of its customers. Zeta will not need to conduct any work on those underlying customers (where the nominee company is regulated in an equivalent jurisdiction) as long as Zeta is able to gain comfort that there are sufficient processes in place at the nominee company to onboard those underlying customers.</p>

    <h4>Required Information</h4>
    <p>Under Zeta's regulations, the letter must contain information to assure Zeta as to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>The entity's risk-grading procedures, including the ability to differentiate between the onboarding requirements for high-risk and low-risk customers; and</li>
      <li>The entity's application of appropriate and effective due diligence measures in respect of its customers, including enhanced measures for PEPs and other high risk relationships.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Additional Information</h4>
    <p>In addition, Zeta may request information to assure Zeta as to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>The entity's ongoing monitoring of the customers;</li>
      <li>The entity's use of sanctions and adverse media screening;</li>
      <li>The entity's training of its staff;</li>
      <li>The entity's processes as to reporting of suspicions;</li>
      <li>The entity's application of source of wealth and source of funds controls;</li>
      <li>The entity's acceptance of so-called 'shell banks' as customers; and</li>
      <li>The entity's application of a compliance monitoring programme to monitor their ongoing compliance with their local regulations.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Zeta has produced a templated Countering Financial Crime Letter that is available on request.</p>
  </dd>
</dl>`;

